INSTALLATION AND BASIC USAGE
============================

All commands below assume execution from the artifact root.

1. Create and activate a Python environment

    python3 -m venv .env
    source .env/bin/activate
    pip install -r requirements.txt

If you only want to run the lightweight open-ended smoke test, you may instead install:

    pip install -r open_ended_dilemma_qualitative_analysis/requirements.txt

2. Offline smoke test (recommended for reviewers)

This test does not require any API key and re-generates the open-ended analysis figures from the packaged adjudicated annotations.

    cd open_ended_dilemma_qualitative_analysis
    python3 visualize_results.py \
      --gpt_csv manually_analyzed_data/resolved_conflict/extracted_gpt4o_checked.csv \
      --llama_csv manually_analyzed_data/resolved_conflict/extracted_llama_checked.csv \
      --out_dir data_visualization
    cd ..

Expected console summary (approximately):

- gpt-4o-mini: mean sensitivity BASE -> OURS = 0.400 -> 0.275
- llama-3.1-8b: mean sensitivity BASE -> OURS = 0.400 -> 0.300

Expected files created under `open_ended_dilemma_qualitative_analysis/data_visualization/`:

- `bias_sensitivity_summary.csv`
- `mean_sensitivity_by_strategy.pdf`
- `change_hist_gpt.pdf`
- `change_hist_llama.pdf`
- `improvements_vs_regressions.pdf`

If those files are created and the summary values above are printed, the installation is functioning correctly.

3. Full controlled-experiment reproduction

Before running the main experiment script, make sure the benchmark files listed in `dataset/README.md` are present.
Then export credentials for the provider(s) you plan to use.

Example:

    export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-..."
    export GROQ_API_KEY="gsk_..."

Baseline example:

    python3 1_compute_bias_sensitivity.py \
      --model gpt-4o-mini \
      --n_independent_runs_per_task 5 \
      --data_model_list gpt-4.1-mini gpt-4o-mini deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b

Recommended mitigation example (sAX + BW):

    python3 1_compute_bias_sensitivity.py \
      --model gpt-4o-mini \
      --self_axioms_elicitation \
      --bias_warning \
      --n_independent_runs_per_task 5 \
      --data_model_list gpt-4.1-mini gpt-4o-mini deepseek-r1-distill-llama-70b

4. Aggregate and visualize RQ1/RQ2 results

    python3 2_visualize_bias_sensitivity.py --self_axioms_elicitation --bias_warning
    python3 3_analyze_strategy_effectiveness.py --show_figures

5. Re-run RQ3 thematic coding analysis

First zip one or more CSV outputs from `generated_output_data/`:

    cd generated_output_data
    zip to_analyze.zip 1_llm_outputs_*.csv
    cd ..

Then run:

    python3 thematic_coding_of_gpai_systems_behaviours/thematic_analysis.py \
      --zip generated_output_data/to_analyze.zip \
      --output_path thematic_coding_of_gpai_systems_behaviours/bias_se_analysis

6. Re-run DevGPT post-hoc validation

Download `DevGPT.zip` separately, then run:

    python3 devgpt_bias_features_analysis/analyze_bias_features_devgpt.py \
      --probe ./dataset \
      --devgpt /path/to/DevGPT.zip \
      --out_dir devgpt_bias_features_analysis/out

Notes
-----
- `run_all_experiments.sh` is a convenience batch runner; it now expects credentials to be provided through environment variables.
- Full API-based reruns may take substantial time and may incur provider charges.
